<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1437981/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" startId="31.[151,250,1896,1918]" targetBox="[151,1436,788,1875]" targetPageId="31">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,1896,1948]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,286,1896,1918]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">FIGURE 11</emphasis>
. Alive 
<taxonomicName authority="(Haan, 1843)" authorityName="Muhammad &amp; Tan &amp; Abdullah &amp; Azirun &amp; Bhaskar &amp; Skejo" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="de Haan" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[375,731,1896,1918]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scelimena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hexodon" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[375,578,1896,1918]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Scelimena hexodon</emphasis>
(Haan, 1843)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[744,866,1896,1918]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[744,866,1896,1918]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
from Tawau Hills Park (Malaysia: Borneo: Sabah). Photograph by Chun Xing Wong Claveria, reproduced with photographer's permission.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,151,501]" box="[151,1320,151,176]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,503,151,176]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Composition and distribution</emphasis>
. Monotypic genus with its only species (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muhammad &amp; Tan &amp; Abdullah &amp; Azirun &amp; Bhaskar &amp; Skejo" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="de Haan" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[964,1093,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scelimena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hexodon">
<emphasis box="[964,1093,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">H. hexodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) inhabiting Borneo.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,266,188,213]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Notes</emphasis>
. The genus is synonymous with 
<emphasis box="[638,761,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1838" box="[638,757,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scelimena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Scelimena</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
This monotypic genus included only 
<taxonomicName authority="(de Haan, 1843)" authorityName="Muhammad &amp; Tan &amp; Abdullah &amp; Azirun &amp; Bhaskar &amp; Skejo" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="de Haan" baseAuthorityYear="1843" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scelimena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hexodon">
<emphasis box="[1188,1319,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">H. hexodon</emphasis>
(de 
<bibRefCitation pageId="32" pageNumber="33" refId="ref37147" refString="Haan, W. (1843) Bijdragen tot de kennis der Orthoptera. Temminck [Ed.] Verhandelingen over de Natuurlijke Geschiedenis der Nederlansche Overzeesche Bezittingen, 19 / 20, 165 - 228." type="journal article">Haan, 1843</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, characteristic in extremely high pronotal projection, forming strong and sharp spines. The genus shares all the morphological characters with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1838" box="[557,672,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scelimena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[557,672,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Scelimena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muhammad &amp; Tan &amp; Abdullah &amp; Azirun &amp; Bhaskar &amp; Skejo" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="de Haan" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[690,818,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scelimena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hexodon">
<emphasis box="[690,818,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">S. hexodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[828,993,260,285]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">comb. resurr.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1012,1095,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1896,1918]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,788,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[151,1436,788,1875]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 11. Alive Scelimena hexodon (Haan, 1843) comb. nov. from Tawau Hills Park (Malaysia: Borneo: Sabah). Photograph by Chun Xing Wong Claveria, reproduced with photographer's permission." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1437981/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) is restricted to Borneo, and 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,347,295,320]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" refId="ref35809" refString="Blackith, R. E. (1992) The Tetrigidae (Insecta; Orthoptera) of South-East Asia; an Annotated Catalogue with Partial Translated Keys and Bibliography. Japaga Press, Dublin, LIV + 249 pp." type="book">Blackith's (1992)</bibRefCitation>
record of the species for 
<collectingRegion box="[650,743,296,320]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
was not confirmed. However, in 
<collectingRegion box="[1136,1232,296,320]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
, a new species is found (
<taxonomicName authority="Muhammad &amp; Tan &amp; Abdullah &amp; Azirun &amp; Bhaskar &amp; Skejo, 2018" authorityName="Muhammad &amp; Tan &amp; Abdullah &amp; Azirun &amp; Bhaskar &amp; Skejo" authorityYear="2018" box="[234,424,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scelimena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[234,424,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Scelimena marta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[432,523,332,357]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[432,523,332,357]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
) closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muhammad &amp; Tan &amp; Abdullah &amp; Azirun &amp; Bhaskar &amp; Skejo" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="de Haan" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[742,867,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scelimena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hexodon">
<emphasis box="[742,867,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">S. hexodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Since the presence of the large spines is the only character separating 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Hancock" authorityYear="1915" box="[382,491,369,392]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Hexocera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[382,491,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Hexocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1838" box="[559,674,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scelimena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[559,674,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Scelimena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(and it is not really separating character), we synonymize 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Hancock" authorityYear="1915" box="[1327,1436,369,392]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Hexocera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="syn. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1327,1436,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Hexocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,256,404,429]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,256,404,429]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">syn. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1838" box="[321,436,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scelimena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[321,436,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Scelimena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Borneo is inhabited by a few species with pronotal projection much larger than in their congers (e.g., 
<emphasis box="[310,770,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Serville" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[310,549,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Discotettix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belzebuth">Discotettix belzebuth</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Hancock" authorityYear="1913" box="[562,770,441,464]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tegotettix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armatus">Tegotettix armatus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
), and so 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muhammad &amp; Tan &amp; Abdullah &amp; Azirun &amp; Bhaskar &amp; Skejo" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="de Haan" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[876,999,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scelimena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hexodon">
<emphasis box="[876,999,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">S. hexodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also have the largest spines within the genus.
</paragraph>
